{"article_id":"FgFZO5DHc75R5h72","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The gun control movement notched a public relations coup with last week ' s massive school walkouts ,","depth":3},{"id":1,"text":"but now school districts","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"that pitched in","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"to ensure the protest ' s success","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"are stuck with the rising political and legal fallout .","depth":4},{"id":5,"text":"A week after the March 14 walkout , school officials are grappling with complaints from parents","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"outraged by the specter of their kids","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"engaged in political protesting on school time ,","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"as well as reports of criminal mischief","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"committed by teens","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"who treated the event as a get-out-of-class-free card .","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"What ' s more , the students get to do it all again next month .","depth":4},{"id":12,"text":"A substantially identical event ,","depth":5},{"id":13,"text":"also called the National School Walkout ,","depth":5},{"id":14,"text":"is scheduled for April 20 , the 19th anniversary of the Columbine High School massacre .","depth":4},{"id":15,"text":"Chris Cleveland , chairman of the Chicago Republican Party , said","depth":6},{"id":16,"text":"he worried","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"that the walkouts ,","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"aimed at pushing for tougher gun restrictions in the wake of the deadly Parkland shooting ,","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"have provided the template for advocacy groups","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"eager to co-opt the public schools for progressive activism .","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"\" If they get away with this ,","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"they ' ll be free to engage in any kind of political activity in the schools","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"that they wish , \"","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"said Mr. Cleveland ,","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"who has a third-grader in the Chicago Public Schools .","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"The party is moving to avert that scenario","depth":7},{"id":27,"text":"by preparing a lawsuit against the school system ,","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"arguing","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"that the district violated state and federal law as well as its own policies","depth":10},{"id":30,"text":"by organizing a political demonstration","depth":12},{"id":31,"text":"- and pressuring students to attend -","depth":12},{"id":32,"text":"on the taxpayers ' dime .","depth":11},{"id":33,"text":"The district has yet to comment ,","depth":6},{"id":34,"text":"but it has other problems .","depth":6},{"id":35,"text":"About 60 students from Simeon Career Academy trashed a Walmart","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"\" while they were supposed to be protesting guns , \"","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"an incident under investigation by police ,","depth":8},{"id":38,"text":"according to Fox32 in Chicago .","depth":7},{"id":39,"text":"The school system issued a statement","depth":8},{"id":40,"text":"saying","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"it was reviewing the incident ,","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"but Mr. Cleveland said","depth":9},{"id":43,"text":"he has yet to receive a response to a letter from the party ' s attorney","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"demanding","depth":11},{"id":45,"text":"\" that they comply with the law . \"","depth":11},{"id":46,"text":"\" There will always be a few kids","depth":11},{"id":47,"text":"who don ' t behave , \"","depth":11},{"id":48,"text":"said Mr. Cleveland .","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"\" I ' m a lot more concerned about the behavior of the adults . \"","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"He is not alone .","depth":4},{"id":51,"text":"Connecticut lawyer Deborah G. Stevenson said","depth":7},{"id":52,"text":"she has fielded calls from parents and others across the nation ,","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"including California , Illinois , Massachusetts and Rhode Island ,","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"after reports about her clash with the New Milford Public Schools .","depth":8},{"id":55,"text":"She urged the district last week on behalf of several parents to cancel the high school walkout ,","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"arguing","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"that the schools had \" condoned , facilitated , and supported an event","depth":10},{"id":58,"text":"that clearly advocates for students to be part of a partisan political ' movement , ' \"","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"but the district refused .","depth":7},{"id":60,"text":"Ms. Stevenson said","depth":7},{"id":61,"text":"her clients plan to pursue further action before the April 20 walkout .","depth":7},{"id":62,"text":"\" Parents are very , very upset about this entire situation , \"","depth":8},{"id":63,"text":"said Ms. Stevenson .","depth":8},{"id":64,"text":"\" The ones","depth":9},{"id":65,"text":"that have contacted us","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"are trying to determine what the proper legal steps would be here .","depth":9},{"id":67,"text":"Everybody ' s trying to make that determination","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"of how and when and where to take the next step . \"","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"While the schools may pay a price for the activism ,","depth":5},{"id":70,"text":"gun control groups are basking in the glow of the walkout ,","depth":6},{"id":71,"text":"which drew as many as 1 million students","depth":7},{"id":72,"text":"and enjoyed widespread press coverage","depth":8},{"id":73,"text":"as Democratic luminaries turned out","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"to cheer on the youthful crowds .","depth":9},{"id":75,"text":"School officials have countered","depth":7},{"id":76,"text":"that walkouts were student-led ,","depth":9},{"id":77,"text":"despite coordination by the Women ' s March youth arm and Action Network ,","depth":9},{"id":78,"text":"and that it was better to use the event as a learning opportunity","depth":9},{"id":79,"text":"rather than watch young people flee the classroom unsupervised .","depth":9},{"id":80,"text":"New Milford Public Schools attorney Michael P. McKeon took umbrage at Ms. Stevenson ' s claim","depth":9},{"id":81,"text":"that the school had engaged in politically motivated behavior ,","depth":9},{"id":82,"text":"insisting","depth":9},{"id":83,"text":"that the events at New Milford High School were voluntary and student-driven .","depth":9},{"id":84,"text":"\" I am sure","depth":10},{"id":85,"text":"that your clients do not consider the murder of students in their schools ' hallways to be political expression , \"","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"Mr. McKeon said in a March 14 letter .","depth":9},{"id":87,"text":"\" Similarly , students","depth":9},{"id":88,"text":"expressing a desire","depth":10},{"id":89,"text":"to be free from the threat of carnage and death in their classrooms can hardly be deemed political speech . \"","depth":10},{"id":90,"text":"He described the event as a \" student-initiated remembrance \" of the 17 people","depth":8},{"id":91,"text":"killed last month at Marjory Stoneman High School in Parkland , Florida ,","depth":8},{"id":92,"text":"and indeed many schools billed the walkout as a memorial .","depth":9},{"id":93,"text":"In some cases , that was true .","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"In other cases , the memorials looked more like rallies ,","depth":9},{"id":95,"text":"stoked by school staff and teachers","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"acting as escorts to events","depth":12},{"id":97,"text":"and providing class time","depth":12},{"id":98,"text":"for making posters","depth":12},{"id":99,"text":"featuring anti-gun slogans .","depth":12},{"id":100,"text":"\" I wouldn ' t say","depth":10},{"id":101,"text":"that every individual school district was partisan ,","depth":10},{"id":102,"text":"but far and wide , it was more than just a memorial service , \"","depth":9},{"id":103,"text":"said Ms. Stevenson .","depth":8},{"id":104,"text":"\" It was a protest with signs ,","depth":10},{"id":105,"text":"with taking positions ,","depth":11},{"id":106,"text":"with leading students to do things ,","depth":13},{"id":107,"text":"to take action ,","depth":13},{"id":108,"text":"selling T-shirts on school grounds","depth":12},{"id":109,"text":"-","depth":9},{"id":110,"text":"that ' s something different than a simple memorial","depth":9},{"id":111,"text":"trying to remember those","depth":10},{"id":112,"text":"who died . \"","depth":10},{"id":113,"text":"Some school officials took a light touch on penalties in support of what was described as a good cause ,","depth":7},{"id":114,"text":"including Chicago Public Schools CEO Janice Jackson ,","depth":8},{"id":115,"text":"who assured students the day before the walkout","depth":9},{"id":116,"text":"that \" We will not enact any disciplinary measures . \"","depth":9},{"id":117,"text":"\" We think","depth":9},{"id":118,"text":"it ' s critically important that the student voice is heard at this crucial point in our history as a nation ,","depth":9},{"id":119,"text":"so we ' ve provided a lot of guidance to our school leaders ,","depth":9},{"id":120,"text":"instructed them on how these things should be conducted ,","depth":10},{"id":121,"text":"and we ' ve also given them the autonomy","depth":11},{"id":122,"text":"to create the best plan at their local schools , \"","depth":11},{"id":123,"text":"she said in a Chicago Sun-Times video .","depth":7},{"id":124,"text":"James Buchal , head of the Multnomah County Republican Party in Oregon , said","depth":9},{"id":125,"text":"Portland Public Schools parents were \" falsely assured","depth":10},{"id":126,"text":"that the protest was not partisan ,","depth":11},{"id":127,"text":"but would constitute a memorial for those slain . \"","depth":11},{"id":128,"text":"\" At the protests , adult participants bragged","depth":12},{"id":129,"text":"about organizing the protest ,","depth":12},{"id":130,"text":"and applauded the help","depth":12},{"id":131,"text":"they had received from PPS , \"","depth":12},{"id":132,"text":"Mr. Buchal said in a Tuesday statement .","depth":10},{"id":133,"text":"\" Organizers made materials available","depth":10},{"id":134,"text":"to support Leftist goals far beyond anti-Second Amendment advocacy . \"","depth":10},{"id":135,"text":"In a statement , Portland Public Schools said","depth":8},{"id":136,"text":"Superintendent Guadalupe Guerrero asked schools to \" treat the day as a ' teachable moment ' \"","depth":9},{"id":137,"text":"and \" structure lesson plans around the theme of safe , supportive and inclusive schools . \"","depth":9},{"id":138,"text":"Other Republicans","depth":9},{"id":139,"text":"who have decried the walkouts","depth":9},{"id":140,"text":"include South Carolina Gov . Henry McMaster ,","depth":9},{"id":141,"text":"who accused organizers of using children as a tool","depth":10},{"id":142,"text":"to further their agenda ,","depth":10},{"id":143,"text":"and former Rep. Tom Tancredo of Colorado ,","depth":9},{"id":144,"text":"who said","depth":10},{"id":145,"text":"he was shocked by the \" open partisanship of classroom teachers","depth":11},{"id":146,"text":"promoting walkouts . \"","depth":11},{"id":147,"text":"\" School administrators , too , participated in the charade , \"","depth":10},{"id":148,"text":"Mr. Tancredo said in a Tuesday op-ed in Colorado Politics .","depth":10},{"id":149,"text":"\" How else to explain the large number of school buses","depth":10},{"id":150,"text":"providing taxpayer-funded transportation to partisan rallies off the campus ? \"","depth":10},{"id":151,"text":"Some districts are also feeling the heat over their approach to student security .","depth":8},{"id":152,"text":"Mr. Buchal said","depth":10},{"id":153,"text":"Portland parents were so concerned about youths","depth":12},{"id":154,"text":"pouring into the streets","depth":12},{"id":155,"text":"that they \" made multiple requests for police backup","depth":12},{"id":156,"text":"to protect students during the event . \"","depth":12},{"id":157,"text":"The Portland school district said","depth":10},{"id":158,"text":"students were not permitted to leave school grounds","depth":11},{"id":159,"text":"and those","depth":14},{"id":160,"text":"who did","depth":14},{"id":161,"text":"were told","depth":13},{"id":162,"text":"they would receive unexcused absences .","depth":12},{"id":163,"text":"In New London , Connecticut , a brouhaha erupted","depth":9},{"id":164,"text":"after Harbor Elementary School kindergartners were led outside on an impromptu \" school safety \" walkout","depth":11},{"id":165,"text":"without written parental permission ,","depth":11},{"id":166,"text":"prompting a board of education member to call for the principal to resign .","depth":10},{"id":167,"text":"Those safety fears were justified in Minneapolis ,","depth":9},{"id":168,"text":"where a student","depth":12},{"id":169,"text":"waving a \" Trump \" flag","depth":12},{"id":170,"text":"was assaulted outside Southwest High School by eight other students .","depth":11},{"id":171,"text":"Fox News reported","depth":11},{"id":172,"text":"that he was taken to urgent care afterward for injuries to his arm .","depth":11},{"id":173,"text":"At least one school organization anticipated the potential","depth":8},{"id":174,"text":"for education to spill into advocacy .","depth":8},{"id":175,"text":"The National School Boards Association issued in February a guidance , \" Navigating Student Walkouts & Mass Protests , \"","depth":9},{"id":176,"text":"that urged school districts to tell staff to avoid political posturing and viewpoint discrimination .","depth":9},{"id":177,"text":"\" Communicate state law and local policies","depth":11},{"id":178,"text":"that may restrict public employee political expression while on duty ,","depth":11},{"id":179,"text":"as well as any specific district directives","depth":11},{"id":180,"text":"that have been issued","depth":12},{"id":181,"text":"regarding the present controversy , \"","depth":12},{"id":182,"text":"said the association .","depth":9},{"id":183,"text":"As far as Ms. Stevenson is concerned ,","depth":8},{"id":184,"text":"the schools fell short ,","depth":8},{"id":185,"text":"and she wants to make sure","depth":8},{"id":186,"text":"it doesn ' t happen again in April .","depth":8},{"id":187,"text":"\" Right now , we ' ve gotten a lot of support from across the country ,","depth":8},{"id":188,"text":"so we ' re trying to assess and coordinate and determine what our next move is ,","depth":8},{"id":189,"text":"but we ' re not going to let it go , \"","depth":8},{"id":190,"text":"she said .","depth":9},{"id":191,"text":"\" Absolutely not . \"","depth":9}],"relations":[{"parent":383,"left":206,"right":382,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":206,"left":196,"right":205,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":196,"left":0,"right":195,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":195,"left":194,"right":4,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":194,"left":1,"right":193,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":193,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":205,"left":202,"right":204,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":202,"left":201,"right":11,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":201,"left":198,"right":200,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":198,"left":5,"right":197,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":197,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":200,"left":8,"right":199,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":199,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":204,"left":203,"right":14,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":203,"left":12,"right":13,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":382,"left":259,"right":381,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":259,"left":240,"right":258,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"par